{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>In late 2018, we made improvements to how we get maps on <a href=\"https://www.boston.gov/\">boston.gov</a>. We wrote about the updates on the Digital Team's blog: <a href=\"https://www.boston.gov/news/building-better-maps-bostongov\">Building better maps for boston.gov</a>.</p>\n<p>From a technical stand point, we leveraged <a href=\"https://github.com/CityOfBoston/patterns/tree/develop/web-components/map\">web components</a> that we wrapped up in a custom Drupal component. The web component uses <a href=\"https://esri.github.io/esri-leaflet/\">esri-leafet</a> which lets us integrate with our data hosted on <a href=\"http://boston.maps.arcgis.com/home/index.html\">ArcGIS Online</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"imageBlock\">\n    <div>\n        <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/c5bac/maps-blog-post.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 500px;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 54.93741307371349%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"Figure 1\" title src=\"/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/81124/maps-blog-post.png\" srcset=\"/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/bcdc2/maps-blog-post.png 125w,\n/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/812ad/maps-blog-post.png 250w,\n/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/81124/maps-blog-post.png 500w,\n/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/2aa1d/maps-blog-post.png 750w,\n/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/1ec8c/maps-blog-post.png 1000w,\n/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/346cf/maps-blog-post.png 1500w,\n/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/c5bac/maps-blog-post.png 2876w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\">\n  </span>\n  </a>\n            <p>\n                <span style=\"font-weight: 600\">Figure 1:</span> Study area is\n                shown along with large-scale mines, regional borders, rivers, and the\n                major geological formations running throughout the area.\n            </p>\n    </div>\n</div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Maps on boston.gov"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/projects/maps-boston-gov/"}}